<p><b>Twitter</b> is an online <a href="/wiki/Social_networking_service" title="Social networking service">social networking service</a> and <a href="/wiki/Microblogging" title="Microblogging">microblogging</a> service that enables its users to send and read text-based posts of up to 140 <a href="/wiki/Character_(computing)" title="Character (computing)">characters</a>, known as "tweets". It was created in March 2006 by <a href="/wiki/Jack_Dorsey" title="Jack Dorsey">Jack Dorsey</a> and launched that July. The service rapidly gained worldwide popularity, with over 300 million users as of 2011,<sup id="cite_ref-cnn_users_5-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-cnn_users-5"><span>[</span>6<span>]</span></a></sup> generating over 300 million tweets and handling over 1.6 billion <a href="/wiki/Web_search_query" title="Web search query">search queries</a> per day.<sup id="cite_ref-twitter-blog-august-update_2-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-twitter-blog-august-update-2"><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-7" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-7"><span>[</span>8<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-8" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-8"><span>[</span>9<span>]</span></a></sup> It has been described as "the <a href="/wiki/SMS" title="SMS">SMS</a> of the <a href="/wiki/Internet" title="Internet">Internet</a>."<sup id="cite_ref-9" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-9"><span>[</span>10<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>Twitter Inc. is based in San Francisco, with additional servers and offices in New York City.</p>
